@startuml
title Optional Architecture (Not Selected for MVP): Firestore Sync + Postgres SoR
actor Technician
participant "Mobile App\n(Firestore SDK + Local Cache)" as Mobile
participant "Firestore Cloud\n(Real-Time DB)" as Firestore
participant "API Gateway\n(Backend Services)" as API
participant "Postgres DB\n(System of Record)" as Postgres
participant "Supervisor Dashboard\n(Real-Time Listener)" as Dashboard

== Offline Update ==

Technician -> Mobile: Update Work Order\n(status, notes, meter readings)
Mobile -> Mobile: Write to Local Cache\n(offline mode)
Mobile -> Mobile: Queue write for sync\n(waiting for network)

== Network Restored ==

Mobile -> Firestore: Sync queued writes\n(status, notes, readings)
Firestore --> Mobile: ACK (synced)

== Backend Sync to Postgres ==

Firestore -> API: Trigger webhook / event\n(workorder_id, updated_fields)
API -> Postgres: INSERT INTO workorder_events\n(status, notes, readings, timestamp)
Postgres --> API: event_id
API -> Firestore: Update doc\n{synced_to_postgres: true}

== Real-Time Broadcast ==

Firestore -> Dashboard: Push update\n(status, technician_location)
Firestore -> Mobile: Push update\n(latest state)

@enduml
